<p>&#8220;If we do not want to slide towards illiberalism, no one should be above the law.&#8221;<span id="more-53291"></span></p>
<div id="attachment_53292" style="width: 677px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-53292" class=" wp-image-53292" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/hunt-luke-congress-2025.png" alt="" width="667" height="425" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/hunt-luke-congress-2025.png 1602w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/hunt-luke-congress-2025-300x191.png 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/hunt-luke-congress-2025-1024x653.png 1024w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/hunt-luke-congress-2025-768x489.png 768w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/hunt-luke-congress-2025-1536x979.png 1536w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/hunt-luke-congress-2025-400x255.png 400w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /><p id="caption-attachment-53292" class="wp-caption-text">Professor Luke Hunt testifying in Congress</p></div>
<p>That&#8217;s <a href="http://www.lukewilliamhunt.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Luke Hunt</a>, associate professor of philosophy at the University of Alabama, during his testimony before the House Judiciary Committee&#8217;s Subcommittee on Oversight, on the Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI) and the rule of law.</p>
<p>Before becoming a philosophy professor, Dr. Hunt was an FBI agent.</p>
<p>In his testimony, Dr. Hunt says that the FBI &#8220;should be an agency that promotes the rule of law,&#8221; and raises &#8220;three concerns about the current state of affairs that could lead to an erosion of the rule of law.&#8221;</p>
<p>These concerns are: arbitrariness in what the FBI investigates, the selective enforcement of corruption, and the influence of politics in responding to national security threats.</p>
